⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Rebellion
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦The Rebellion:BKZ:3082d1⟧

WHO   — The Rebellion — returning the ticket
WHAT  — The strongest statement of the problem of evil in fiction: Ivan does not deny God but ‘most respectfully returns the ticket’ to a heaven priced in a child's tears.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel insists on facing the hardest case for unbelief at full strength — and on not pretending to refute it.
HOW   — By piling up, coldly and unbearably, true accounts of cruelty to children, and declining the ticket to harmony at that price.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  If the price of eternal harmony is one tortured child's tears, then I return the ticket — and no argument in the book is given to take it back.

